dct_description_sm: Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (AM), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army , original map compiled by USGS 1947. Alternate title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Beech Grove, Indiana. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3763 II NE. Edition: AMS 1. Transverse Mercator projection. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, schools, churches, cemeteries, mines, and natural features. Marginal maps: Index to boundaries -- Index to adjoining sheets. Contour interval 10 feet. Army Map Service , V851. "Scale changed, marginal data revised and Universal Transverse Mercator Grid added, 1948. Copied in 1948 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Beech Grove, 1947. Original map compiled by USGS 1947, from plane-table surveys and stereophotogrammetric methods, 1946. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC & GS." "N3937.5-W8600/7.5." "AMS 1, 1948." Printed with vegetation.
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army, 1948.
Dimensions: 56 x 45 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:25,000
dct_creator_sm: Geological Survey (U.S.); United States. Army Map Service
